modules.description: This module implements runtime support for assertion checks in generated code, providing functions to test predicates, equality, and result expectations with detailed positional tracking. It operates on values of arbitrary type `'a`, using sexp conversion and comparison functions to report discrepancies in test failures. It is used to validate conditions and compare expected versus actual outcomes in testing scenarios.

Implements runtime support for assertion checks in generated code, offering functions to validate predicates, equality, and result expectations with detailed positional tracking. Works with values of arbitrary type `'a` using sexp conversion and comparison to report discrepancies during test failures. Used to enforce conditions and compare expected versus actual outcomes in testing scenarios.
